1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:08,006
<i>[ Clicking ]</i>                    


2
00:00:17,785 --> 00:00:19,884
WHY AM I HERE, SYDNEY?          


3
00:00:19,953 --> 00:00:22,020
        I WANT YOU TO EXAMINE   
        SOME PHOTOGRAPHS.       


4
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:26,558
                IS HE A WARRIOR?


5
00:00:26,627 --> 00:00:29,828
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>                
<i>YES, A SOLDIER</i>                  
<i>IN SOUTHEAST ASIA.</i>              


6
00:00:29,897 --> 00:00:32,697
                WHY DO I HAVE TO
                LOOK AT HIM?    


7
00:00:32,766 --> 00:00:36,468
THERE ARE PEOPLE                
WHO BELIEVE THIS PHOTOGRAPH     
WAS MANUFACTURED,               


8
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:38,470
        CREATED.                


9
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:40,538
I WANT TO KNOW WHAT YOU THINK.  


10
00:00:43,143 --> 00:00:45,677
                    HE'S AFRAID,


11
00:00:45,746 --> 00:00:47,746
                        SAD.    


12
00:00:49,349 --> 00:00:51,883
[ Young Sydney ]                
HE'S MISSING.                   


13
00:00:51,952 --> 00:00:54,753
THE PEOPLE WHO LOVE HIM WANT    
TO KNOW IF HE'S STILL ALIVE.    


14
00:00:58,025 --> 00:01:00,025
                LIKE MY PARENTS?


15
00:01:00,094 --> 00:01:03,295
<i>[ Gunfire ]</i>                     


16
00:01:03,364 --> 00:01:06,365
<i>[ Gunfire Continues ]</i>           


17
00:01:15,108 --> 00:01:17,909
    WHY ARE YOU SO INTERESTED   
    IN MR. STARR?               


18
00:01:17,978 --> 00:01:20,245
        [ Miss Parker ]         
        IT'S A FAMILY MATTER.   


19
00:01:20,314 --> 00:01:24,482
COULD YOU DESCRIBE              
HIS MANNER, HIS MOOD,           
YOU KNOW?                       


20
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:26,484
UH, I TELL YOU--                


21
00:01:26,553 --> 00:01:28,787
THAT OL' BOY                    
WAS MULTIFACETED.               


22
00:01:28,856 --> 00:01:33,492
HE WALKED IN HERE, AND HE       
DIDN'T KNOW A PICKLE BARREL     
FROM A GUN BARREL.              


23
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,560
AND IN LESS THAN 24 HOURS--     


24
00:01:37,330 --> 00:01:40,598
    [ Laughing ]                


25
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:42,600
HE'S DOING THIS.                


26
00:01:44,037 --> 00:01:46,405
10:19.                          


27
00:01:46,473 --> 00:01:49,140
THEY'RE ALL LIKE THIS.          


28
00:01:49,210 --> 00:01:51,509
    DAMNED IF I KNOW            
    WHAT IT MEANS.              


29
00:01:51,578 --> 00:01:55,080
    -<i> OH, AND THEN</i>              
     <i> THERE WAS THE SLUGS.</i>      
    - WHAT ABOUT THE SLUGS?     


30
00:01:55,148 --> 00:01:58,650
<i>HE PAID EXTRA TO COME IN</i>        
<i>AFTER HOURS AND DIG 'EM</i>         
<i>OUT THE BACK WALL.</i>              


31
00:01:58,718 --> 00:02:03,455
SAID HE WANTED TO STUDY 'EM.    
HE WAS REAL BIG                 
ON STUDYIN' THINGS.             


32
00:02:03,524 --> 00:02:05,323
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>                    


33
00:02:05,392 --> 00:02:08,460
    - LIKE I SAY, THIS OL' BOY  
      WAS MULTIFACETED.         
    - MULTIFACETED.             


34
00:02:08,528 --> 00:02:11,663
        <i> [ Laughing ]</i>           
        <i> DID HE HAPPEN TO SAY</i>   
        <i> WHERE HE WAS GOING?</i>    


35
00:02:11,732 --> 00:02:15,434
HE WAS STAYING AT THE LODGE     
UP NEAR THE HIGHWAY.            
YOU MIGHT CHECK THERE.          


36
00:02:15,503 --> 00:02:17,669
                    THANK YOU.  
SURE ENOUGH.                    


37
00:02:17,738 --> 00:02:20,138
                CAN I?          
FREE COUNTRY.                   
OH, HEY!                        


38
00:02:22,609 --> 00:02:24,942
<i>WHEN YOU FIND HIM,</i>              
<i>GIVE HIM HIS TOY.</i>               


39
00:02:25,011 --> 00:02:26,979
                HIS TOY?        


40
00:02:27,047 --> 00:02:31,116
<i>YEAH. WHEN HE WAS THROUGH</i>       
<i>SHOOTING, HE'D RUN THAT</i>         
<i>ALL AROUND THE PLACE.</i>           


41
00:02:31,184 --> 00:02:33,118
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>                    


42
00:02:33,187 --> 00:02:36,621
THAT OL' BOY WAS JUST           
A BIG KID, THAT'S ALL.          
FUNNY, HUH?                     


43
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:39,958
        - HYSTERICAL.           
        - HERE.                 


44
00:02:40,026 --> 00:02:42,193
            [ Whirring ]        


45
00:02:43,797 --> 00:02:45,730
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>               


46
00:02:49,302 --> 00:02:52,470
<i>[ Siren Continues ]</i>             


47
00:02:54,808 --> 00:02:56,742
                [ Siren Stops ] 


48
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:58,944
        [ Police Radio Chatter, 
          Indistinct ]          


49
00:03:05,152 --> 00:03:08,019
    WAS I GOING TOO FAST        
    WHEN I PASSED THAT TRUCK?   
                        NO, SIR.


50
00:03:09,957 --> 00:03:11,890
        WHEN YOU PASSED ME.     


51
00:03:11,959 --> 00:03:15,460
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


52
00:04:06,045 --> 00:04:08,546
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>I WANT MY LAWYER.</i>               
<i>I GOT RIGHTS!</i>                   


53
00:04:08,615 --> 00:04:11,116
            YOU BETTER RELAX.   
             YOU HEAR ME?       


54
00:04:11,184 --> 00:04:13,818
        SHUT UP AND DON'T MOVE. 


55
00:04:13,887 --> 00:04:17,054
    WANT A BEER OR CAPPUCCINO   
    OR SOMETHING?               
HA-HA.                          


56
00:04:17,123 --> 00:04:19,624
            LET'S SEE           
            WHAT WE GOT HERE.   


57
00:04:19,693 --> 00:04:22,894
    OH, BOY! A BONA FIDE        
    THREE-TIME LOSER, FRANKIE.  


58
00:04:22,962 --> 00:04:24,896
            WE KNOW WHAT THAT   
            MEANS, DON'T WE?    


59
00:04:24,964 --> 00:04:27,399
AUTOMATIC JAIL TIME, ISN'T IT?  
                CONGRATULATIONS.


60
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:29,400
            THOUGH IT DOES SEEM 
            A LITTLE HARSH,     


61
00:04:29,469 --> 00:04:31,936
        CONSIDERING THAT YOU GOT
        ONLY-- WHAT?            


62
00:04:32,005 --> 00:04:35,774
        SIX DOLLARS AND 37 CENTS
        OFF AN OLD LADY.        


63
00:04:35,843 --> 00:04:38,242
            YOU ALMOST GOT AWAY 
            WITH IT TOO.        


64
00:04:38,311 --> 00:04:40,912
    YOU ARE WHAT WE CALL        
    A TOP-NOTCH CRIMINAL.       
    WHERE'S MY COFFEE, FRANK?   


65
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:43,014
        <i> RUN, YOU LITTLE PUKE!</i>  


66
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:45,750
        - [ Grunts ]            
        - OW!                   


67
00:04:45,819 --> 00:04:49,154
    MAN, MAYBE I SHOULD'VE      
    GOT HIM A DECAF.            


68
00:04:49,222 --> 00:04:53,024
THAT LOOKED LIKE IT HURT.       
    SEE WHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU   
    ACT LIKE AN IDIOT?          


69
00:04:53,093 --> 00:04:55,861
            PUT THE TRACK STAR  
            IN HIS CAGE.        
DON'T RIP THAT PRETTY SHIRT.    


70
00:04:55,929 --> 00:04:59,364
- SLICK MOVE. CARL BISHOP.      
- HOW YOU DOIN'? FRANK MEYERS.  


71
00:04:59,432 --> 00:05:01,532
JAROD STARR.                    
TWO R's.                        


72
00:05:01,601 --> 00:05:04,102
        - HEY, LIKE RINGO.      
        - WHO'S RINGO?          


73
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:07,238
THAT'S FUNNY.                   
HOW COME I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU     
AROUND HERE BEFORE?             


74
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:09,507
        HE JUST TRANSFERRED IN  
        FROM CHICAGO.           


75
00:05:09,576 --> 00:05:12,743
        YOU'RE LATE AGAIN TODAY,
        AND I'M STILL WAITING ON
        THOSE TRANSFER PAPERS.  


76
00:05:12,812 --> 00:05:16,948
I WAS COMING TO TALK TO YOU--   
BISHOP, MEYERS, YOU TWO WERE DUE
IN MY OFFICE A HALF HOUR AGO.   


77
00:05:17,016 --> 00:05:19,217
            YEAH. WELL, WE'VE   
            BEEN KIND OF BUSY.  


78
00:05:19,286 --> 00:05:22,787
- I WANT YOU BOTH INSIDE NOW.   
<i>- DETECTIVE, GIVE US A BREAK.</i>   
<i>  WE'VE GONE OVER THIS ALREADY.</i> 


79
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:25,990
        NOW.                    


80
00:05:26,059 --> 00:05:29,461
THAT WOMAN NEEDS A HOBBY.       
                SHE'S JUST DOING
                HER JOB, FRANK. 


81
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:31,563
- WE'LL SEE YOU LATER, CHICAGO. 
- LOOK FORWARD TO IT.           


82
00:05:31,631 --> 00:05:33,632
<i>[ Meyers ]</i>                      
<i>YEAH, NICE MEETING YOU.</i>         


83
00:05:35,201 --> 00:05:38,870
    - DID I MISS SOMETHING?     
    - TYPICAL I.A. FROST.       


84
00:05:38,938 --> 00:05:42,907
    - SHE'S INTERNAL AFFAIRS?   
    - DETECTIVE KAREN SWINDELL. 


85
00:05:42,976 --> 00:05:45,243
            DON'T GET ANY IDEAS,
            ROMEO.              


86
00:05:45,312 --> 00:05:48,012
        SHE'S THE ORIGINAL      
        ICE PRINCESS.           


87
00:05:48,082 --> 00:05:50,882
    YOU WERE SAYING SOMETHING   
    ABOUT TRANSFER PAPERS.      
COME ON, SARGE.                 


88
00:05:50,951 --> 00:05:53,384
YOU KNOW HOW IT IS              
WITH RED TAPE. THEY SHOULD      
BE ALONG ANY DAY NOW.           


89
00:05:53,453 --> 00:05:55,854
        UNTIL I GET THE REST    
        OF YOUR DOCUMENTATION,  


90
00:05:55,923 --> 00:05:58,423
            YOU'RE GONNA        
            BE RIDING A DESK    
            INSTEAD OF A BIKE.  


91
00:05:58,491 --> 00:06:00,925
        YOU DON'T WANT ME       
        TO START THINKING       
        YOU'RE UP TO SOMETHING. 


92
00:06:00,994 --> 00:06:04,662
ME? SARGE,                      
I'M CLEAN AS A WHISTLE.         


93
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:06,765
        GET BACK TO WORK.       


94
00:06:09,002 --> 00:06:10,902
    [ Tires Screeching ]        
    [ Horn Honking ]            


95
00:06:10,971 --> 00:06:13,437
            [ Siren Wailing ]   


96
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:29,587
    CAN I HELP YOU, OFFICER?    


97
00:06:31,324 --> 00:06:34,392
MA'AM, DID YOU, BY ANY CHANCE,  
HAPPEN TO NOTICE THE COLOR--    


98
00:06:34,460 --> 00:06:37,595
WHOA! IS THAT A TWIN CAM?       


99
00:06:37,664 --> 00:06:43,000
                    EXCUSE ME?  
YOU GUYS BORE OUT               
THE CYLINDER HEADS, DON'T YOU?  


100
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:46,938
MAN, I'D LOVE TO SOUP UP        
MY HONEYPOT.                    


101
00:06:47,006 --> 00:06:49,174
                YOUR HONEYPOT?  
    MY HOG.                     


102
00:06:49,243 --> 00:06:53,578
I WAS GOIN' TO                  
BLOW OUT THE HEADERS            
AND OPEN UP THE CYLINDER BLOCK, 


103
00:06:53,647 --> 00:06:56,481
BUT MY SOCIAL SECURITY CHECK    
WAS LATE.                       


104
00:06:56,549 --> 00:06:59,383
    -<i> MILLIE!</i>                   
    - HEY, MILL!                
      YOU'RE LOOKIN' GOOD!      


105
00:06:59,452 --> 00:07:04,256
    RIDE... YOU DEVILS!         
    [ Laughing ]                


106
00:07:05,659 --> 00:07:08,159
RODE WITH THOSE DUDES           
IN JACKSONVILLE.                


107
00:07:08,227 --> 00:07:11,395
                        MA'AM.  
MILDRED REYNOLDS.               


108
00:07:11,464 --> 00:07:13,631
FRIENDS CALL ME MILLIE.         
                        MILLIE. 


109
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:17,635
    DID YOU HAPPEN TO NOTICE    
    THE COLOR OF THE LIGHT BACK 
    THERE IN THE INTERSECTION?  


110
00:07:21,575 --> 00:07:23,508
WHAT LIGHT?                     


111
00:07:34,221 --> 00:07:37,088
WONDER BOY CHECKED OUT OF THIS  
DIRT-WATER TOWN THREE DAYS AGO. 


112
00:07:37,157 --> 00:07:40,692
            THAT'S ALL          
            HE LEFT BEHIND.     
            WHERE'S THE DRIVER? 


113
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:43,327
USING THE FACILITY.             


114
00:07:43,396 --> 00:07:48,066
    GUY HAS THE BLADDER         
    OF A SQUIRREL.              
[ Siren Chirping ]              


115
00:07:48,135 --> 00:07:50,135
                HMM. WHAT NOW?  


116
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,215
        - AFTERNOON, MISSY.     
        - SHERIFF.              


117
00:08:05,218 --> 00:08:08,986
        WOULD YOU MIND          
        TAKING OFF YOUR JACKET? 
    EXCUSE ME?                  


118
00:08:09,055 --> 00:08:12,057
OH, IT'S NOTHING PERSONAL.      
I'D JUST LIKE YOU TO TAKE OFF   
YOUR JACKET, PLEASE.            


119
00:08:13,226 --> 00:08:15,660
    I WILL NOT.                 
                        PLEASE. 


120
00:08:21,568 --> 00:08:23,902
                <i> [ Miss Parker ]</i>
                <i> YOU ARE FIRED!</i> 


121
00:08:26,406 --> 00:08:28,673
I WANT YOU TO KNOW              
I'VE SEEN<i> DELIVERANCE.</i>          


122
00:08:31,812 --> 00:08:34,646
            YOU WANNA GIVE ME   
            ONE OF THESE?       


123
00:08:34,714 --> 00:08:37,248
        OH! THAT'S GOOD ENOUGH. 
        MY, MY!                 


124
00:08:38,584 --> 00:08:41,485
            GUESS YOU           
            CAN PUT SOME CUFFS  
            ON THIS YOUNG LADY. 


125
00:08:41,554 --> 00:08:45,190
    MA'AM, YOU'RE UNDER ARREST  
    FOR VIOLATION OF            
    THE CRIMINAL CODE 369.7.    


126
00:08:45,258 --> 00:08:47,192
AND WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?      


127
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:51,563
<i>CARRYING A CONCEALED WEAPON.</i>    
<i>IT SAYS SO RIGHT HERE</i>           
<i>IN THE BOOK.</i>                    


128
00:08:51,632 --> 00:08:53,632
<i>HIGHLIGHTED IN YELLOW.</i>          


129
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:56,167
            <i> [ Sheriff ]</i>        
            <i> I GUESS YOU'LL BE</i>  
            <i> GOING WITH ME.</i>     


130
00:08:56,236 --> 00:08:58,069
            JAROD.              
            [ Exhales ]         


131
00:08:58,137 --> 00:09:00,271
    SO LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.


132
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:03,441
            <i> THIS</i> STARTS OUT    
             AS A PART OF THIS, 


133
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:06,544
    BUT THEN YOU PUNCH IT OUT,  
    AND YOU SELL IT             
    AS A SEPARATE PRODUCT.      


134
00:09:06,612 --> 00:09:10,548
I THINK YOU GOT IT.             
DOUGHNUT. DOUGHNUT HOLE.        


135
00:09:10,617 --> 00:09:14,552
            I DON'T MEAN        
            TO BELABOR A POINT, 


136
00:09:14,621 --> 00:09:18,957
        BUT IF THE HOLE IS HERE,
        WHY DO YOU CALL THIS    
        THE HOLE?               


137
00:09:19,025 --> 00:09:21,826
THE TRUTH IS, I'VE ALWAYS       
WONDERED THAT MYSELF.           


138
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:25,296
BUT DON'T TELL MY BOSS.         
I WOULDN'T WANT HIM TO THINK    
I DON'T KNOW THE BUSINESS.      


139
00:09:25,365 --> 00:09:27,932
            I PROMISE.          
            AND I'LL HAVE       
            ANOTHER ONE, PLEASE.


140
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:30,234
ON THE HOUSE.                   


141
00:09:30,303 --> 00:09:33,304
OH. IF YOU DON'T MIND,          
I'D RATHER EAT IT HERE.         


142
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,713
<i>GOOD MORNING,</i>                   
<i>MR. KEMBROOK!</i>                   


143
00:09:51,157 --> 00:09:53,958
HE SEEMS VERY SAD.              


144
00:09:54,027 --> 00:09:57,661
<i>[ Woman ] POOR MAN.</i>             
<i>HE HASN'T BEEN THE SAME</i>         
<i>SINCE MARVIN WAS KILLED.</i>        


145
00:09:57,730 --> 00:10:00,465
    MARVIN.                     
                    <i> HIS SON.</i>   


146
00:10:00,533 --> 00:10:02,667
        HE WAS A GUARD          
        AT THE BOSWELL JEWELERS.


147
00:10:02,736 --> 00:10:05,469
            ABOUT A MONTH AGO,  
            HE WAS SHOT         
            TRYING TO ROB IT.   


148
00:10:05,538 --> 00:10:08,305
SOUNDS LIKE YOU KNOW            
THE FAMILY PRETTY WELL.         


149
00:10:08,374 --> 00:10:11,509
        HMM. SINCE I WAS BORN.  


150
00:10:11,578 --> 00:10:13,644
            MR. KEMBROOK ANYWAY.


151
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:16,447
I'M AFRAID                      
YOU'VE LOST ME.                 


152
00:10:16,516 --> 00:10:20,284
    THE KEMBROOKS GAVE MARVIN   
    UP FOR ADOPTION             
    WHEN HE WAS JUST A BABY.    


153
00:10:20,353 --> 00:10:24,088
A FEW YEARS AFTER               
MRS. KEMBROOK DIED, MR. KEMBROOK
STARTED SEARCHING FOR HIS SON.  


154
00:10:24,157 --> 00:10:27,291
- FOUND HIM SIX MONTHS AGO.     
- HE MUST HAVE BEEN VERY HAPPY. 


155
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,327
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>THEY BOTH WERE.</i>                 


156
00:10:29,396 --> 00:10:32,463
<i>TURNS OUT MARVIN</i>                
<i>WAS LOOKING FOR HIS PARENTS</i>     
<i>THE WHOLE TIME TOO.</i>             


157
00:10:32,532 --> 00:10:35,966
CAN YOU IMAGINE MEETING YOUR    
OWN PARENTS FOR THE FIRST TIME  
WHEN YOU'RE A GROWN ADULT?      


158
00:10:36,035 --> 00:10:38,869
    GUESS IT WOULD BE           
    PRETTY EMOTIONAL.           


159
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:41,272
            <i> OH, YEAH.</i>          


160
00:10:41,341 --> 00:10:44,509
    EVEN AFTER ALL THOSE YEARS, 
    THEY STILL LOVED EACH OTHER.


161
00:10:44,577 --> 00:10:47,411
    WHAT MAKES YOU SO SURE?     


162
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:51,182
    <i> BECAUSE THEY WERE BLOOD,</i>   
    <i> AND THERE'S NOTHING</i>        
    <i> STRONGER THAN THAT.</i>        


163
00:10:55,656 --> 00:10:57,655
<i>[ Door Bells Jingling ]</i>         


164
00:11:40,299 --> 00:11:44,902
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>MRS. MORGAN, WE MAY HAVE</i>        
<i>A SIGHTING ON YOUR DAUGHTER.</i>    


165
00:11:44,971 --> 00:11:48,473
    <i> MY PEOPLE ARE FLYING</i>       
    <i> TO NEW YORK AS WE SPEAK.</i>   


166
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:51,842
    <i> IF ALL GOES WELL,</i>          
    <i> YOU SHOULD HAVE YOUR ARMS</i>  
    <i> AROUND CATHERINE...</i>        


167
00:11:51,911 --> 00:11:54,545
            <i> BY TOMORROW NIGHT.</i> 


168
00:11:54,614 --> 00:11:57,482
            THANK YOU.          
            GOD BLESS YOU TOO.  


169
00:12:03,056 --> 00:12:05,456
            HOW CAN I HELP YOU? 


170
00:12:12,865 --> 00:12:14,866
I DON'T KNOW WHO I AM.          


171
00:12:22,274 --> 00:12:25,175
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>NOW, LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.</i>  


172
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:29,114
    YOU STOPPED ME BECAUSE OF   
    AN ANONYMOUS PHONE CALL?    


173
00:12:29,182 --> 00:12:31,182
<i>[ Sheriff ]</i>                     
<i>UH-HUH.</i>                         


174
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,919
    <i> DO YOU MIND TELLING ME</i>     
    <i> HOW YOU KNEW THIS PERSON</i>   
    <i> WAS TELLING THE TRUTH?</i>     


175
00:12:34,988 --> 00:12:37,388
HE SOUNDED HONEST.              


176
00:12:39,225 --> 00:12:42,460
            IT'S OFFICIAL.      
            I'M IN HELL!        


177
00:12:42,529 --> 00:12:45,296
OH, NOW, DARLIN',               
YOU DID HAVE THAT               
CONCEALED WEAPON ON YOU,        


178
00:12:45,365 --> 00:12:49,366
<i>AND YOU'LL BE ABLE TO POST BAIL</i> 
<i>AS SOON AS JUDGE HARGRAVE GET</i>   
<i>BACK FROM THAT BASS TOURNAMENT,</i> 


179
00:12:49,436 --> 00:12:51,269
AND WE SIGN OURSELVES           
SOME PAPERS.                    


180
00:12:51,337 --> 00:12:54,706
    - WHEN EXACTLY IS THAT?     
    - DAY AFTER TOMORROW.       


181
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:57,775
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>THANKS.</i>                         


182
00:13:01,381 --> 00:13:03,948
THE ENTIRE LEGAL STAFF          
AT THE CENTRE...                


183
00:13:04,016 --> 00:13:08,386
IS ON THEIR ANNUAL RETREAT      
IN THE SOUTH OF FRANCE,         


184
00:13:08,455 --> 00:13:13,023
SO IT WILL BE                   
AT LEAST 72 HOURS BEFORE WE     
CAN EVEN REACH A LAWYER.        


185
00:13:14,026 --> 00:13:15,960
                HE KNEW THAT.   


186
00:13:16,029 --> 00:13:19,196
        DAMN IT, SYDNEY.        
        HE'S UP TO SOMETHING.   


187
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:24,001
            AND HE NEEDS ME     
            OUT OF THE WAY      
            FOR THREE DAYS.     


188
00:13:24,070 --> 00:13:26,537
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>10:19.</i>                          


189
00:13:26,606 --> 00:13:28,739
<i>COULD BE A TIME REFERENCE.</i>      


190
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:30,809
                FORGET THAT!    


191
00:13:32,612 --> 00:13:35,713
        JUST GET ME A LAWYER.   


192
00:13:35,782 --> 00:13:37,715
                ANY LAWYER.     


193
00:13:37,784 --> 00:13:41,919
<i>[ Granger ]</i>                     
<i>MOST MISSING PERSONS CASES FALL</i> 
<i>INTO ONE OF THREE CATEGORIES:</i>   


194
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:45,323
        <i> ABDUCTIONS, RUNAWAYS</i>   
        <i> OR ABANDONMENT.</i>        


195
00:13:47,927 --> 00:13:50,428
I'M LOOKING FOR MY PARENTS.     


196
00:13:51,698 --> 00:13:54,031
            WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
            I CAN HELP?         


197
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:57,668
I READ IN THE PAPER THAT YOU    
HELPED REUNITE A FATHER AND SON 
AFTER 25 YEARS.                 


198
00:13:57,737 --> 00:14:00,838
        <i> FRIENDLY WARNING:</i>      
        <i> THEY DON'T ALL TURN OUT</i>
        <i> THAT WAY.</i>              


199
00:14:00,906 --> 00:14:03,874
THERE'S A RISK A PERSON TAKES   
WHEN THEY SEARCH FOR THEIR PAST.


200
00:14:03,943 --> 00:14:06,277
            <i> IT'S NOT ALWAYS</i>    
            <i> WHAT THEY HOPE FOR.</i>


201
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:09,380
I'D BE WILLING TO RISK ANYTHING 
FOR THE CHANCE TO FIND OUT.     


202
00:14:09,449 --> 00:14:11,882
        ARE THEY STILL ALIVE?   


203
00:14:15,187 --> 00:14:18,556
    <i> [ Young Sydney ]</i>           
    <i> JAROD, IS HE STILL ALIVE?</i>  


204
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:21,659
                    THE EYES.   


205
00:14:21,728 --> 00:14:24,896
        <i> WHAT ABOUT THE EYES?</i>   


206
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:27,932
                HE WANTS TO CRY,


207
00:14:28,001 --> 00:14:30,234
                BUT HE CAN'T.   


208
00:14:30,303 --> 00:14:32,236
                    WHY NOT?    


209
00:14:32,305 --> 00:14:35,873
    <i> HE FEELS ALONE, FORGOTTEN.</i> 


210
00:14:35,941 --> 00:14:37,941
            HE JUST DOESN'T CARE
            ANYMORE.            


211
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:41,912
            CARE ABOUT WHO?     
<i>HIMSELF.</i>                        


212
00:14:41,981 --> 00:14:43,982
        HE'S GIVEN UP.          


213
00:14:47,787 --> 00:14:50,521
    I WON'T GIVE UP, SYDNEY.    


214
00:14:52,025 --> 00:14:54,592
        [ Echoing ]             
        I'LL NEVER GIVE UP.     


215
00:14:54,660 --> 00:14:56,660
                <i> OFFICER STARR?</i> 


216
00:14:58,465 --> 00:15:01,765
                        <i> JAROD.</i> 
            HMM?                


217
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:06,003
    I WAS WONDERING             
    IF YOU KNEW IF YOUR PARENTS 
    WERE STILL ALIVE.           


218
00:15:11,078 --> 00:15:13,644
I WAS NEVER TOLD THE TRUTH.     


219
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:18,083
WHY NOT USE THE POLICE DATABASE 
TO INITIATE A SEARCH?           


220
00:15:18,151 --> 00:15:20,084
                        I CAN'T.


221
00:15:20,154 --> 00:15:23,621
    THIS IS PROBABLY GONNA      
    BE HARD TO UNDERSTAND,      
    BUT I DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME. 


222
00:15:23,690 --> 00:15:27,492
            <i> SEVENTY-TWO HOURS.</i> 
    WITHOUT A NAME--            


223
00:15:27,561 --> 00:15:30,095
            I HAVE A PICTURE.   


224
00:15:31,264 --> 00:15:33,331
            THIS IS MY MOTHER.  


225
00:15:34,935 --> 00:15:36,868
                AT LEAST THAT'S 
                WHAT I WAS TOLD.


226
00:15:36,937 --> 00:15:38,869
        AND MY FATHER MIGHT HAVE
        BEEN AN AVIATOR.        


227
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:43,474
        - IN THE SERVICE?       
        - I DON'T KNOW.         


228
00:15:43,543 --> 00:15:46,444
    - I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN DO.   
    - THANK YOU.                


229
00:15:49,582 --> 00:15:51,515
OFFICER STARR.                  


230
00:15:51,584 --> 00:15:55,853
        <i> THERE'S A GROUP--</i>      
        <i> PEOPLE LIKE YOURSELF.</i>  


231
00:15:55,922 --> 00:15:59,357
        THERE'S A MEETING HERE  
        TOMORROW NIGHT          
        IF YOU'RE INTERESTED.   


232
00:15:59,425 --> 00:16:03,094
            SOMETIMES IT HELPS  
            JUST TO KNOW        
            YOU'RE NOT ALONE.   


233
00:16:08,534 --> 00:16:10,468
                    [ Sighs ]   
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>                 


234
00:16:34,194 --> 00:16:36,328
            <i> [ Man Laughing ]</i>   


235
00:16:39,933 --> 00:16:43,668
            MISS PARKER.        
            YOU WANTED A LAWYER?


236
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:49,240
HENRY?                          
                OH.             
                [ Chuckling ]   


237
00:16:49,308 --> 00:16:51,543
TELL ME YOU'RE KIDDING.         


238
00:16:51,612 --> 00:16:55,013
            HENRY J. MONROE JR.,
            ESQUIRE.            


239
00:16:55,082 --> 00:16:57,348
                FINEST ATTORNEY 
                IN CEDAR POINT. 


240
00:16:57,417 --> 00:17:00,551
            TRUTH BE KNOWN,     
            THE ONLY ATTORNEY   
            IN CEDAR POINT.     


241
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:02,553
            [ Wheezing Laugh ]  


242
00:17:05,559 --> 00:17:07,391
    HE KNEW THIS.               


243
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:09,994
        <i> [ Desk Sergeant ]</i>      
        <i> MA'AM, THERE'S NOTHING</i> 
        <i> I CAN DO.</i>              


244
00:17:10,063 --> 00:17:14,699
    <i> YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.</i>      
    <i> THIS IS A DEATH SENTENCE</i>   
    <i> FOR ME.</i>                    


245
00:17:14,768 --> 00:17:17,835
            - MILLIE?           
            - WHAT?             


246
00:17:17,904 --> 00:17:21,739
            FINALLY! SOMEONE    
            WITH HALF A BRAIN   
            IN THEIR HEAD.      


247
00:17:21,808 --> 00:17:24,542
    YOU KNOW THIS WOMAN?        
WE'VE MET.                      


248
00:17:24,611 --> 00:17:27,878
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?             
                    I, UH--     


249
00:17:27,947 --> 00:17:31,682
    I ACCIDENTALLY SIDESWIPED   
    A MEAT WAGON...             


250
00:17:31,751 --> 00:17:33,751
            DOWN ON             
            BISCAYNE BOULEVARD. 


251
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:38,189
    NOW THEY WANT TO PUT ME     
    IN CEMENT BOOTS AND DUMP ME 
    INTO THE CAUSEWAY.          


252
00:17:38,258 --> 00:17:40,758
    SHE RAN AN EMPTY COUNTY     
    AMBULANCE OFF THE ROAD,     


253
00:17:40,827 --> 00:17:43,661
    AND WE'RE SUSPENDING        
    HER DRIVER'S LICENSE.       


254
00:17:44,664 --> 00:17:47,332
CAN YOU GIVE US                 
A MOMENT, PLEASE?               


255
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,400
        BE MY GUEST.            


256
00:17:51,338 --> 00:17:54,171
    I WOULDN'T TRUST THAT ONE   
    AS FAR AS I CAN THROW HER.  


257
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:57,475
MILLIE,                         
THIS IS VERY SERIOUS.           


258
00:17:57,544 --> 00:18:01,546
WHAT IF THAT AMBULANCE          
WAS CARRYING SOMEBODY           
TO THE HOSPITAL?                


259
00:18:06,052 --> 00:18:08,686
            GEEZ, I DON'T WANT  
            TO HURT ANYBODY.    


260
00:18:13,593 --> 00:18:15,860
            LOOK, MY, UH--      


261
00:18:15,929 --> 00:18:18,496
            MY HUSBAND'S DEAD,  


262
00:18:18,565 --> 00:18:20,698
    AND MY KIDS ARE ALL GONE.   


263
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,767
        THEY'RE ON THEIR OWN.   


264
00:18:24,971 --> 00:18:28,439
            I'M 73 YEARS OLD,   


265
00:18:28,508 --> 00:18:31,208
            AND I'M ALONE.      


266
00:18:33,947 --> 00:18:37,248
            YOU TAKE MY BIKE,   


267
00:18:37,317 --> 00:18:40,285
    YOU TAKE MY INDEPENDENCE.   


268
00:18:43,189 --> 00:18:46,424
<i>YOU TAKE THAT,</i>                  
<i> YOU MIGHT AS WELL BURY ME...</i>   


269
00:18:46,493 --> 00:18:49,327
            'CAUSE I'LL--       
            I'LL BE DEAD.       


270
00:18:56,135 --> 00:19:00,471
        A LOVELY RUBY, EMERALD  
        AND SAPPHIRE TRIO...    


271
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:02,507
        BORDERED BY DIAMONDS.   


272
00:19:02,575 --> 00:19:05,577
    HOW MUCH IS IT?             
                <i> ONLY $4,000.</i>   


273
00:19:05,645 --> 00:19:07,979
HMM. THAT'S NOT ENOUGH.         


274
00:19:09,149 --> 00:19:12,650
        WELL, I DO HAVE         
        THIS BRILLIANT...       


275
00:19:12,718 --> 00:19:16,187
            PRINCESS-CUT DIAMOND
            WITH A TRILLION     
            ON EITHER SIDE...   


276
00:19:16,255 --> 00:19:18,189
                FOR 5,000.      


277
00:19:18,258 --> 00:19:21,759
    WITH TAX                    
    THAT WOULD BE 5,328.        


278
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:23,695
THAT'S PERFECT.                 


279
00:19:23,763 --> 00:19:26,063
    I'LL TAKE IT.               


280
00:19:36,409 --> 00:19:40,744
    YOU DO REALIZE THIS PURCHASE
    IS GOING TO MAX OUT         
    YOUR CREDIT CARD.           


281
00:19:40,813 --> 00:19:42,746
    THAT'S THE IDEA.            


282
00:20:00,099 --> 00:20:02,033
        [ Chuckling ]           


283
00:20:12,411 --> 00:20:16,180
<i>[ TV: Indistinct ]</i>              


284
00:20:16,249 --> 00:20:18,782
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>AN ODYSSEY OF SEARCHING</i>         
<i>FOR THE PAST...</i>                 


285
00:20:18,852 --> 00:20:22,586
    CAME TO A DRAMATIC          
    AND EMOTIONAL CONCLUSION    
    EARLIER THIS MORNING...     


286
00:20:22,655 --> 00:20:26,790
AS HAROLD KEMBROOK              
NERVOUSLY WAITED FOR THE DOORS  
OF THE TAXI TO OPEN...          


287
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:29,360
    AND DELIVER HIS SON,        
    GIVEN UP FOR ADOPTION...    


288
00:20:29,428 --> 00:20:31,529
<i>SOME 25 YEARS EARLIER.</i>          


289
00:20:31,598 --> 00:20:33,530
    AS FATE WOULD HAVE IT,      


290
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,600
    HIS SON,                    
    MARVIN HOWARD KEMBROOK,     


291
00:20:35,668 --> 00:20:39,870
    HAD SPENT THE LAST 11 YEARS 
    ON THE VERY SAME HUNT...    


292
00:20:39,939 --> 00:20:42,506
<i>FOR HIS TRUE IDENTITY.</i>          


293
00:20:44,110 --> 00:20:47,244
    ALSO ON HAND TO WITNESS     
    THE EMOTIONAL REUNION...    


294
00:20:47,313 --> 00:20:49,680
        WAS SUSAN GRANGER,      


295
00:20:49,749 --> 00:20:53,117
<i>THE WOMAN INSTRUMENTAL</i>          
<i>IN BRINGING THE TWO MEN</i>         
<i>TOGETHER, FATHER AND--</i>          


296
00:20:53,185 --> 00:20:55,185
<i>[ TV: Off ]</i>                     


297
00:21:09,736 --> 00:21:11,802
<i>[ Knocking On Door ]</i>            


298
00:21:13,105 --> 00:21:15,105
                JUST A SECOND.  


299
00:21:23,015 --> 00:21:25,883
                    YOU STARR?  
THAT'S ME.                      


300
00:21:25,952 --> 00:21:28,586
    YOU ORDERED THE DOUGHNUTS.  


301
00:21:30,356 --> 00:21:33,124
RASPBERRY SUPREMES?             
            WHATEVER.           


302
00:21:38,365 --> 00:21:40,565
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>MMM! THIS SHOULD COVER IT.</i>      


303
00:21:40,634 --> 00:21:43,467
                HEY.            


304
00:21:43,536 --> 00:21:46,270
            I'M GONNA GO OUT    
            ON A REAL LIMB HERE 
            AND TAKE A GUESS... 


305
00:21:46,339 --> 00:21:48,338
            THAT YOU'RE         
            A BIG DOUGHNUT FAN? 


306
00:21:48,407 --> 00:21:52,076
THEY'RE VERY GOOD.              
                WHAT ARE YOU,   
                LIKE, A COP?    


307
00:21:52,145 --> 00:21:54,445
HOW DID YOU KNOW?               


308
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:57,414
                THAT'S FUNNY.   


309
00:22:01,254 --> 00:22:03,254
            DETECTIVE SWINDELL? 


310
00:22:03,323 --> 00:22:05,989
    I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND       
    IF I SKIP THE BIRTHDAY SONG.


311
00:22:06,058 --> 00:22:08,359
            I NEVER ACTUALLY    
            LEARNED THE WORDS.  


312
00:22:08,428 --> 00:22:12,696
YOU READ MY FILE.               
THAT'S MY JOB.                  
        IT'S A BAVARIAN CREAM.  


313
00:22:12,765 --> 00:22:15,866
I WAS THINKING ABOUT            
GETTING YOU A RASPBERRY SUPREME,
BUT SOMEBODY ATE THE LAST ONE.  


314
00:22:15,935 --> 00:22:19,103
                BUT THIS ONE'S  
                VERY GOOD.      


315
00:22:19,172 --> 00:22:21,672
MOST UNIFORMS DON'T WANT        
TO SOCIALIZE WITH I.A.          


316
00:22:21,741 --> 00:22:25,743
THE TRUTH IS, I'M THINKING      
ABOUT PUTTING IN FOR A TRANSFER 
TO INTERNAL AFFAIRS,            


317
00:22:25,811 --> 00:22:28,712
AND THE EXAMINATION REQUIRES    
THAT THE APPLICANT BREAK DOWN   
AN ACTUAL CASE FILE--           


318
00:22:28,781 --> 00:22:31,716
    - AND YOU WANT MY HELP.     
    - I HEARD YOU WERE          
      VERY THOROUGH.            


319
00:22:31,784 --> 00:22:35,452
UH, DO YOU HAVE ANY             
PARTICULAR CASE IN MIND?        


320
00:22:35,521 --> 00:22:37,187
                    YES, I DO.  


321
00:22:40,026 --> 00:22:43,027
                ARE YOU GOING   
                TO EAT THAT?    


322
00:22:44,797 --> 00:22:47,799
            SO, ACCORDING TO    
            THE FIELD REPORT,   


323
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:51,869
    BISHOP AND MEYERS           
    RESPONDED TO A ROBBERY CALL 
    AT THE JEWELRY STORE.       


324
00:22:51,938 --> 00:22:54,939
            WHEN THEY GET THERE,
            A SECURITY GUARD,   
            MARVIN KEMBROOK,    


325
00:22:55,008 --> 00:22:57,008
            IS ROBBING          
            THE PLACE...        


326
00:22:57,076 --> 00:22:59,110
            WITH AN ACCOMPLICE. 


327
00:22:59,179 --> 00:23:02,180
            SO THIS ACCOMPLICE  
            SHOOTS KEMBROOK,    


328
00:23:02,248 --> 00:23:04,381
        AND THEN HE GETS AWAY.  


329
00:23:04,450 --> 00:23:08,452
    THIS SOUNDS MORE LIKE       
    AN UNSOLVED HOMICIDE THAN   
    AN I.A. INVESTIGATION.      


330
00:23:08,521 --> 00:23:11,255
FORENSICS                       
WENT OVER THAT STORE            
WITH A FINE-TOOTH COMB.         


331
00:23:11,324 --> 00:23:13,825
THEY DIDN'T FIND A PRINT,       
A FIBER, NOTHING.               


332
00:23:13,893 --> 00:23:17,061
            SO THIS ACCOMPLICE  
            WAS EFFICIENT.      
[ Chuckles ]                    


333
00:23:17,130 --> 00:23:20,298
IF YOU'RE EVER GONNA MAKE IT    
IN I.A., YOU HAVE TO REALIZE    
THAT PART OF THE JOB...         


334
00:23:20,366 --> 00:23:23,801
IS TO GET INSIDE THE HEADS      
OF THE PEOPLE INVOLVED          
IN THE CASE.                    


335
00:23:23,870 --> 00:23:27,504
<i>MARVIN KEMBROOK SPENT MOST</i>      
<i>OF HIS LIFE IN FOSTER HOMES.</i>    


336
00:23:27,574 --> 00:23:30,575
WHEN HE WAS 18,                 
HE JOINED THE MARINES.          
I LOOKED UP HIS MILITARY FILE.  


337
00:23:30,643 --> 00:23:33,343
HE TESTED IN THE LOWEST         
FIVE PERCENT OF HIS UNIT,       


338
00:23:33,412 --> 00:23:35,913
SPENT 10 YEARS IN UNIFORM       
AND NEVER BUSTED CORPORAL.      


339
00:23:35,981 --> 00:23:38,215
        NOT EXACTLY             
        A CRIMINAL MASTERMIND.  


340
00:23:38,284 --> 00:23:41,352
<i>WE'RE TALKING ABOUT A YOUNG MAN</i> 
<i>WHO JUST FOUND OUT WHO HE WAS,</i>  


341
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:43,420
<i>WHERE HE CAME FROM.</i>             


342
00:23:43,489 --> 00:23:46,323
    HE HAD $2,000               
    IN HIS BANK ACCOUNT.        
    HIS BILLS WERE PAID.        


343
00:23:46,392 --> 00:23:49,126
    YOU WANT TO TELL ME         
    HE'D THROW ALL THAT AWAY    
    FOR A FAST SCORE?           


344
00:23:49,195 --> 00:23:52,530
    SO IF YOU DON'T THINK       
    THAT KEMBROOK WAS INVOLVED, 


345
00:23:52,598 --> 00:23:55,199
        AND THE ACCOMPLICE      
        WAS FICTITIOUS,         


346
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,201
            WHO DID IT?         


347
00:23:57,269 --> 00:23:59,771
THERE WAS ONE PIECE OF HARD     
EVIDENCE LEFT AT THE SCENE--    


348
00:23:59,839 --> 00:24:02,339
THE SLUG THEY DUG OUT           
OF MARVIN KEMBROOK'S CHEST.     


349
00:24:02,408 --> 00:24:05,476
FIND THE GUN                    
THAT FIRED THAT BULLET,         
AND YOU FIND THE REAL KILLER.   


350
00:24:09,182 --> 00:24:11,348
    OH, MAN!                    
<i>[ Toilet Flushing ]</i>             


351
00:24:11,417 --> 00:24:13,484
        WHAT, YOU'RE LATE AGAIN,
        HUH?                    


352
00:24:13,553 --> 00:24:17,355
THE DESK SARGE IS GONNA         
HAVE MY BUTT IN A SLING         
IF SHE CATCHES ME.              


353
00:24:17,424 --> 00:24:19,424
CAN YOU DO ME A FAVOR?          
                WHAT'S UP?      


354
00:24:19,492 --> 00:24:22,026
MY TRANSFER PAPERS              
GOT SENT TO MY HOUSE            
BY MISTAKE.                     


355
00:24:22,095 --> 00:24:25,329
WOULD YOU GIVE THEM TO HER,     
AFTER I'M GONE?                 


356
00:24:25,398 --> 00:24:27,398
                    NO PROBLEM. 
        THANKS.                 


357
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:30,401
HEY, LISTEN. YOU KNOW,          
I'M KIND OF NEW AROUND HERE     
AND DON'T KNOW MANY PEOPLE.     


358
00:24:30,470 --> 00:24:33,471
I WAS THINKING MAYBE I COULD    
TAKE YOU AND YOUR PARTNER       
TO LUNCH ONE DAY.               


359
00:24:33,539 --> 00:24:35,339
MY TREAT.                       
            YEAH, SURE.         
            HOW 'BOUT TOMORROW? 


360
00:24:35,408 --> 00:24:37,975
GREAT.                          
I LOOK FORWARD TO IT.           
                ALL RIGHT, MAN. 


361
00:24:51,290 --> 00:24:54,892
HEY, PARTNER.                   
HOW'S IT GOING?                 
                ALL RIGHT, BRO. 


362
00:24:54,961 --> 00:24:59,463
        READ THIS. I THINK      
        WE FOUND THE GUY        
        WE'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR. 


363
00:24:59,532 --> 00:25:01,532
YEAH?                           


364
00:25:09,742 --> 00:25:12,676
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>IT'S BEEN ALMOST 11 YEARS...</i>    


365
00:25:12,746 --> 00:25:15,546
    <i> SINCE MY SON DISAPPEARED,</i>  


366
00:25:15,615 --> 00:25:18,149
        <i> AND THERE ISN'T A DAY</i>  
        <i> THAT GOES BY...</i>        


367
00:25:18,218 --> 00:25:20,684
            <i> THAT I DON'T THINK</i> 
            <i> I SEE HIM,</i>         


368
00:25:20,753 --> 00:25:24,155
        STANDING                
        ON A STREET CORNER...   


369
00:25:24,224 --> 00:25:27,058
                OR PASSING BY   
                ON A CITY BUS.  


370
00:25:28,661 --> 00:25:32,296
    MY FRIENDS, THEY ALL SAY,   
    "YOU SHOULD LET IT GO."     


371
00:25:32,365 --> 00:25:35,199
    BUT, I MEAN,                
    HOW DO YOU DENY YOURSELF?   


372
00:25:35,267 --> 00:25:39,270
    HOW DO YOU JUST...          
    WALK AWAY FROM YOUR LIFE?   


373
00:25:41,974 --> 00:25:43,974
                    <i> YOU DON'T.</i> 


374
00:25:47,646 --> 00:25:51,282
        WE'VE BEEN COMING HERE  
        FOR MORE YEARS          
        THAN I WANT TO REMEMBER,


375
00:25:51,350 --> 00:25:55,519
    MORE YEARS THAN ANY OF US   
    WANT TO ADMIT.              


376
00:25:55,588 --> 00:25:59,357
    YOU PEOPLE KNOW MY STORY,   
    WHAT HAPPENED TO MY SON.    


377
00:25:59,425 --> 00:26:04,228
<i>[ Woman's Voice Overlapping ]</i>   
    I'M HERE TO TELL YOU THAT   
    YOU SHOULD NEVER GIVE UP.   


378
00:26:04,297 --> 00:26:08,299
    NEVER STOP LOOKING FOR      
    THE PEOPLE THAT YOU LOVE    
    BECAUSE IT'S WORTH IT,      


379
00:26:09,735 --> 00:26:12,536
            EVEN IF IT'S        
            FOR JUST A MOMENT.  


380
00:26:14,274 --> 00:26:17,375
        <i> YOU KNOW,</i>              
        <i> WE SIT HERE AND WE...</i>  


381
00:26:17,443 --> 00:26:21,412
            <i> TALK ABOUT HOW MUCH</i>
            <i> WE MISS THEM AND...</i>


382
00:26:21,481 --> 00:26:23,481
        <i> HOW MUCH WE LOVED THEM.</i>


383
00:26:23,550 --> 00:26:26,050
    IN THE END, I THINK IT'S--  


384
00:26:28,521 --> 00:26:31,855
<i>I THINK IT'S THE LITTLE THINGS</i>  
<i>THAT WE MISS THE MOST.</i>          


385
00:26:33,659 --> 00:26:37,094
    THE WAY WE SEE OURSELVES    
    IN OUR CHILDREN.            


386
00:26:37,163 --> 00:26:40,097
    [ Voices Overlapping ]      
    THE WAY HE SAT IN A CHAIR.  


387
00:26:40,166 --> 00:26:42,599
            HIS LAUGH.          


388
00:26:46,539 --> 00:26:49,106
        THE WAY HE STIRRED      
        HIS COFFEE.             


389
00:26:54,947 --> 00:26:56,947
<i>[ Jarod's Mother's Voice ]</i>      
<i>NEVER GIVE UP...</i>                
        NEVER GIVE UP...        


390
00:26:57,016 --> 00:26:59,950
<i>EVER.</i>                           
                        <i> EVER.</i>  


391
00:27:07,827 --> 00:27:10,694
            [ Siren Wailing ]   
<i>[ Man ] AH, BABY, YOU ARE</i>       
<i>BUMMING MY TRIP, MAN.</i>           


392
00:27:10,763 --> 00:27:13,965
<i>[ Millie ]</i>                      
<i>PINT-SIZED NERD!</i>                
<i>NERD? I'M REAL, MAN.</i>            


393
00:27:14,033 --> 00:27:16,633
<i>[ Millie ]</i>                      
<i>YOU WEREN'T LOOKING</i>             
<i>WHERE YOU WERE GOING!</i>           


394
00:27:16,702 --> 00:27:20,704
<i>I WASN'T GOING ANYWHERE.</i>        
        YOU DON'T HAVE TO YELL. 
        I'M NOT DEAF.           


395
00:27:20,773 --> 00:27:23,274
NO, YOU'RE BLIND, LADY.         
YOU GOTTA TAKE A CHILL--        


396
00:27:23,342 --> 00:27:26,343
WELL, I WANNA TELL YOU.         
YOU JUST BETTER HAVE            
A LITTLE RESPECT!               


397
00:27:26,412 --> 00:27:31,315
- WHAT SEEMS TO BE THE TROUBLE? 
- FEEBLE KNIEVEL HERE ALMOST CUT
  ME IN HALF WITH HER TRICYCLE. 


398
00:27:31,384 --> 00:27:35,019
YOU LITTLE PUNK!                
    OKAY, OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.     
    THAT IS ENOUGH.             


399
00:27:35,087 --> 00:27:38,221
        THAT IS ENOUGH.         
        YOU, STAY HERE.         


400
00:27:38,290 --> 00:27:40,290
    YOU, COME WITH ME.          


401
00:27:43,396 --> 00:27:45,763
                LOOK AT THAT.   


402
00:27:45,831 --> 00:27:47,831
        IS THAT IT?             
                        YEAH.   


403
00:27:47,901 --> 00:27:51,569
IT'S NOTHING THAT A LITTLE      
SANDPAPER AND TOUCH-UP PAINT    
WON'T CURE.                     


404
00:27:51,637 --> 00:27:55,305
YOU DO HAVE INSURANCE?          
    YEAH, BUT I'M NOT GONNA LET 
    THAT OLD BAG GET AWAY.      


405
00:27:55,374 --> 00:27:57,307
        SHE ALMOST WASTED ME,   
        MAN.                    


406
00:27:57,376 --> 00:27:59,977
            WHAT HAVE WE HERE?  


407
00:28:00,045 --> 00:28:02,045
                <i> AN EXPIRED</i>     
                <i> LICENSE PLATE.</i> 


408
00:28:02,114 --> 00:28:04,648
        THAT'S GONNA COST YOU   
        ABOUT A HUNDRED BUCKS   
        IN FINES.               


409
00:28:04,717 --> 00:28:08,018
        AND I COULD, OF COURSE, 
        SEARCH YOUR VAN.        


410
00:28:08,087 --> 00:28:11,221
SANDPAPER                       
AND TOUCH-UP PAINT ON--         
                        MM-HMM. 


411
00:28:13,225 --> 00:28:15,293
        HAVE A NICE DAY.        


412
00:28:17,229 --> 00:28:21,499
        <i> AND YOU, YOUNG LADY,</i>   
        <i> YOU'RE COMING WITH ME.</i> 
OH. WHERE?                      


413
00:28:21,567 --> 00:28:23,500
                        THERE.  


414
00:28:23,569 --> 00:28:26,369
<i>[ Meyers ]</i>                      
<i>SO WHAT DID YOUR WIFE</i>           
<i>DO NEXT?</i>                        


415
00:28:26,438 --> 00:28:29,773
        <i> SHE WALKS IN,</i>          
        <i> SHE PACKS HER BAGS,</i>    
        <i> AND THEN SHE SPLITS.</i>   


416
00:28:29,842 --> 00:28:32,143
OUCH.                           
        YOU GOTTA BE KIDDING ME.


417
00:28:32,211 --> 00:28:35,112
            WHY WOULD I MAKE UP 
            A STORY LIKE THAT?  
    THEY ARE SO UNBELIEVABLE.   


418
00:28:35,181 --> 00:28:38,549
IT'S INCREDIBLE. NEXT TIME      
I TALKED TO HER, WE WERE IN SOME
LAWYER'S OFFICE, 100 BUCKS PER. 


419
00:28:38,618 --> 00:28:41,118
    - SOUNDS LIKE MY LAST WIFE. 
    - OH, NO.                   


420
00:28:41,186 --> 00:28:43,420
    - MARRIAGE NUMBER THREE?    
    - NO. FOUR.                 


421
00:28:43,489 --> 00:28:46,223
            FOUR? GEEZ!         
            WHAT, YOU GOT, LIKE,
            A THOUSAND KIDS?    


422
00:28:46,292 --> 00:28:48,726
- NO, SIX. SIX REAL GOOD KIDS.  
- AND THEY DON'T LOOK LIKE HIM. 


423
00:28:48,794 --> 00:28:50,527
SHUT UP, FRANK.                 


424
00:28:50,596 --> 00:28:53,631
    MUST BE TOUGH               
    MAKING ENDS MEET,           
    WITH ALL THOSE OBLIGATIONS. 


425
00:28:53,699 --> 00:28:55,933
I MAKE SURE EVERYBODY'S         
WELL TAKEN CARE OF.             


426
00:28:56,002 --> 00:28:59,903
                STILL, YOU KNOW,
                THERE'S GOTTA BE
                A BETTER WAY.   


427
00:28:59,972 --> 00:29:04,208
    - WHAT, LIKE CHICAGO?       
    - CHICAGO?                  


428
00:29:04,276 --> 00:29:07,311
    YEAH, WE KNOW ABOUT         
    THE INVESTIGATION,          


429
00:29:07,379 --> 00:29:10,481
<i>THE PAYOFF MONEY YOU WERE</i>       
<i>COLLECTING FROM THE DEALERS</i>     
<i>ON THE SOUTH SIDE.</i>              


430
00:29:10,549 --> 00:29:14,051
    - YOU READ MY FILE.         
    - NEW GUY COMES IN,         
      WE CHECK HIM OUT.         


431
00:29:14,119 --> 00:29:16,053
    YOU'D DO THE SAME THING.    


432
00:29:16,122 --> 00:29:19,123
            YOU HAD NO RIGHT    
            TO READ MY FILE.    


433
00:29:19,191 --> 00:29:22,326
            BESIDES, THEY NEVER 
            PROVED ANYTHING.    


434
00:29:22,395 --> 00:29:26,430
IT PROVES THAT YOU              
CAN COVER YOUR TRACKS,          
SO TAKE IT EASY.                


435
00:29:28,501 --> 00:29:31,502
<i>FRANK AND I DO THE JOB,</i>         
<i>BUT WE'RE ALWAYS LOOKING</i>        
<i>FOR NEW OPPORTUNITIES.</i>          


436
00:29:31,571 --> 00:29:33,837
    - ISN'T THAT RIGHT, FRANK?  
    - THAT'S RIGHT.             


437
00:29:33,906 --> 00:29:36,573
TAKES A SPECIAL KIND OF COP     
TO DO WHAT WE DO.               


438
00:29:36,642 --> 00:29:39,143
WE THINK YOU'RE THAT COP.       
THAT'S ALL.                     


439
00:29:44,316 --> 00:29:48,852
            I'M SORRY, SIR.     
            YOUR CREDIT CARD    
            CAME BACK INVALID.  


440
00:29:50,423 --> 00:29:53,157
        THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.      
        TRY RUNNING IT THROUGH  
        THE RIGHT WAY.          


441
00:29:54,493 --> 00:29:57,695
<i>I KNOW HOW TO DO MY JOB.</i>        
<i> I TRIED IT THREE TIMES, OKAY?</i>  


442
00:29:57,763 --> 00:30:00,697
    LOOK, THERE'S SOME MISTAKE, 
    OBVIOUSLY.                  


443
00:30:00,766 --> 00:30:04,468
    -<i> I ALWAYS PAY OFF</i>          
     <i> MY CREDIT CARD.</i>           
    -<i> THERE'S NO MISTAKE.</i>       


444
00:30:04,537 --> 00:30:09,206
<i>FRANK, LOOKS LIKE WE'RE GONNA</i>   
<i>HAVE TO BAIL THIS DEADBEAT OUT</i>  
<i>BEFORE HE PULLS HIS GUN...</i>      


445
00:30:09,275 --> 00:30:12,309
AND TRIES TO SHOOT HIS WAY      
OUT OF HERE.                    


446
00:30:15,447 --> 00:30:18,482
LOOK, I GOTTA TAKE MY KID       
TO LITTLE LEAGUE PRACTICE.      
THANKS, BUDDY.                  


447
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:22,318
DROP BY THE PARK                
IN A COUPLE OF HOURS.           
WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT THEN, OKAY? 


448
00:30:22,388 --> 00:30:24,621
            I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.
YEAH, YOU DO THAT.              


449
00:30:24,690 --> 00:30:27,691
GOT A LITTLE                    
SOMETHING RIGHT HERE.           
THANKS FOR LUNCH.               


450
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:29,760
        YEAH.                   


451
00:30:33,798 --> 00:30:36,333
        <i> [ Granger On Phone ]</i>   
        <i> WE GOT A RED FLAG</i>      
        <i> ON YOUR MOTHER'S PHOTO.</i>


452
00:30:36,402 --> 00:30:39,136
    SOMEPLACE IN DELAWARE.      
                    DELAWARE?   


453
00:30:39,204 --> 00:30:41,804
<i>MEAN ANYTHING TO YOU?</i>           
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>IT USED TO.</i>                     


454
00:30:43,876 --> 00:30:47,477
    WELL, SOMEONE PICKED UP     
    THE GLOBAL SCAN ON THE NET  
    THAT WE SENT OUT.           


455
00:30:47,545 --> 00:30:49,545
        WE GOT AN ANONYMOUS     
        PHONE CALL.             


456
00:30:49,614 --> 00:30:53,016
WHOEVER IT WAS, RECOGNIZED      
THE WOMAN IN THE PICTURE        
AND HAS A NAME,                 


457
00:30:53,085 --> 00:30:57,053
BUT THEY'RE ADAMANT ABOUT       
NOT SENDING ANYTHING OVER THE   
COMPUTER SYSTEM OR PHONE LINES. 


458
00:30:57,122 --> 00:30:59,689
    I MEAN, IT SEEMS STRANGE.   


459
00:30:59,758 --> 00:31:02,259
YOU WANT TO GO FORWARD          
WITH THIS?                      


460
00:31:10,569 --> 00:31:13,003
                    YES.        
                        OKAY.   


461
00:31:13,072 --> 00:31:16,440
THEY'RE SENDING THE INFORMATION 
BY SPECIAL COURIER.             


462
00:31:16,508 --> 00:31:19,375
        I'LL CALL YOU           
        THE SECOND IT GETS HERE.
                    THANK YOU.  


463
00:31:26,518 --> 00:31:29,620
                <i> [ Footsteps ]</i>  
                    <i> [ Woman ]</i>  
                    <i> BROOTS?</i>    


464
00:31:29,688 --> 00:31:32,388
        <i> WE JUST GOT A SIGNAL</i>   
        <i> ALERT ON JAROD.</i>        


465
00:31:32,458 --> 00:31:34,624
    WHERE?                      
        A MISSING PERSONS AGENCY
        IN MIAMI.               


466
00:31:34,693 --> 00:31:38,528
    BUT WE ALSO MONITORED       
    A RESPONSE SIGNAL EMANATING 
    FROM INSIDE THE CENTRE.     


467
00:31:38,597 --> 00:31:41,831
SOMEONE ON THE INSIDE           
MADE CONTACT                    
WITH THIS AGENCY?               


468
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:44,400
WELL, WHAT KIND                 
OF INFORMATION                  
WAS BREACHED?                   


469
00:31:44,469 --> 00:31:47,103
            WE-- WE'RE NOT SURE.


470
00:31:47,172 --> 00:31:49,138
HAS ANYONE ALERTED              
MISS PARKER?                    


471
00:31:49,207 --> 00:31:51,875
                WE THOUGHT      
                YOU'D WANT TO.  


472
00:31:58,984 --> 00:32:02,385
        I'D RATHER STICK MY HEAD
        IN A BEAR TRAP.         


473
00:32:02,454 --> 00:32:05,255
        <i> [ Bat Hitting Ball ]</i>   
                    <i> [ Bishop ]</i> 
                    <i> YEAH!</i>      


474
00:32:05,324 --> 00:32:08,491
    <i> SO HOW MANY OF THESE JOBS</i>  
    <i> HAVE YOU PULLED?</i>           
WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?   


475
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:11,561
WE'RE THROWING YOU A ROPE.      
THE QUESTION IS, ARE YOU        
SMART ENOUGH TO GRAB IT?        


476
00:32:11,629 --> 00:32:14,797
    WHY DO YOU NEED A THIRD GUY?
'CAUSE WE HAD PROBLEMS          
THE LAST TIME OUT.              


477
00:32:14,866 --> 00:32:18,668
WE NEED A THIRD GUY             
TO PLUG UP THE LEAKS.           


478
00:32:18,737 --> 00:32:22,806
            HOW DOES IT WORK?   
    WE USE THE SECURITY CODES   
    SUPPLIED BY THE STORES.     


479
00:32:22,875 --> 00:32:26,309
    - LOW RISK, HIGH REWARD.    
    - OH, YEAH.                 


480
00:32:26,378 --> 00:32:29,513
            WHAT IF SOMETHING   
            GOES WRONG?         
    IT WON'T.                   


481
00:32:29,581 --> 00:32:33,383
            HUMOR ME. WHAT IF   
            SOMEBODY WALKS IN?  


482
00:32:33,452 --> 00:32:35,952
    <i> WE'RE WEARING BLUE.</i>        
     <i> WE'RE THE GOOD GUYS.</i>      


483
00:32:36,020 --> 00:32:38,688
    THEY'RE NOT GONNA SUSPECT US
    OF A CRIME. THEY'LL THINK   
    WE'RE RESPONDING TO ONE.    


484
00:32:38,757 --> 00:32:41,091
        WHAT IF THEY PULL A GUN?
THEN WE TAKE 'EM DOWN.          


485
00:32:41,159 --> 00:32:46,296
I MEAN, WE JUST MAKE IT         
LOOK LIKE, UH, WE STOPPED       
A ROBBERY IN PROGRESS.          


486
00:32:46,365 --> 00:32:49,799
    - WE'RE HOME FREE.          
    - IS THAT WHAT HAPPENED     
      WITH MARVIN KEMBROOK?     


487
00:32:49,868 --> 00:32:53,302
<i>- WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT THAT?</i>  
<i>- [ Jarod ] COME ON.</i>            


488
00:32:53,371 --> 00:32:55,739
        I READ YOUR FILES TOO.  


489
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:59,308
    WHAT I DON'T UNDERSTAND IS, 
    HOW DID YOU TAMPER WITH     
    THE BALLISTIC REPORT?       


490
00:32:59,377 --> 00:33:03,479
- WHAT?                         
-<i> THEY NEVER MADE A MATCH TO THE</i>
<i>  WEAPON THAT KILLED KEMBROOK.</i>  


491
00:33:03,548 --> 00:33:06,416
    INTERNAL AFFAIRS            
    ALWAYS CHECKS THE WEAPONS   
    OF THE FIRST OFFICERS...    


492
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:08,885
        THAT ARRIVE AT THE SCENE
        OF A HOMICIDE.          


493
00:33:11,056 --> 00:33:13,990
    THINK I WAS WRONG           
    ABOUT YOU, JAROD.           
    LET'S GO, FRANK.            


494
00:33:14,058 --> 00:33:16,426
            WHOA, WAIT A MINUTE.


495
00:33:16,494 --> 00:33:18,828
            YOU'RE ASKING ME    
            TO RISK EVERYTHING. 


496
00:33:18,897 --> 00:33:22,231
    ALL I'M ASKING IS,          
    IF SOMETHING GOES WRONG,    


497
00:33:22,300 --> 00:33:24,300
            DO I HAVE A WAY OUT?


498
00:33:29,908 --> 00:33:33,176
THROWAWAY. ANKLE HOLSTER.       
UNREGISTERED.                   


499
00:33:33,245 --> 00:33:37,147
SOMETHING GOES DOWN, WE USE IT. 
PUT IT IN THE TRUNK OF MY CAR,  
WAIT FOR THE HEAT TO BLOW OVER. 


500
00:33:37,216 --> 00:33:39,783
    LOOK, ARE YOU IN OR WHAT?   


501
00:33:40,819 --> 00:33:43,586
            - I'M IN.           
            - GOOD.             


502
00:33:43,655 --> 00:33:45,922
I'M GLAD YOU'RE                 
ON THE TEAM, STARR.             


503
00:33:45,991 --> 00:33:50,093
BUT IF YOU CROSS ME,            
I'LL PUT A BULLET IN YOUR HEART.


504
00:33:52,164 --> 00:33:54,330
DAD! DAD!                       


505
00:33:54,399 --> 00:33:56,800
        LET'S GO!               
        ALL RIGHT!              


506
00:33:56,869 --> 00:33:59,168
TOMMY. ATTABOY.                 
OHH!                            


507
00:33:59,237 --> 00:34:01,771
            YOU LOOKED GREAT    
            OUT THERE.          
WANT ICE CREAM?                 


508
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:03,840
<i>[ Tommy ]</i>                       
<i>YEAH!</i>                           


509
00:34:08,413 --> 00:34:13,416
    I PLAN ON SUING             
    THIS ENTIRE DIRT-WATER TOWN 
    FOR EVERY PENNY IT'S WORTH. 


510
00:34:13,485 --> 00:34:16,019
            MY CARD.            
STANTON.                        


511
00:34:16,087 --> 00:34:18,721
    - LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.    
    - OH, MISS PARKER.          


512
00:34:18,790 --> 00:34:21,958
<i>DO YOU KNOW A MAN</i>               
<i>BY THE NAME OF BROOTS?</i>          
        TAKE A MESSAGE.         


513
00:34:22,027 --> 00:34:24,293
HE SAYS HE LOCATED THE TARGET!  


514
00:34:30,101 --> 00:34:32,935
                <i> GRACIAS.</i>       
    <i> DE NADA.</i>                   


515
00:34:48,286 --> 00:34:51,888
<i>[ Jarod's Mother's,</i>             
<i>Kembrook's Voices ]</i>             
<i>HIS LAUGH.</i>                      


516
00:34:51,957 --> 00:34:54,457
<i>THE WAY HE STIRRED</i>              
<i>HIS COFFEE.</i>                     


517
00:35:36,234 --> 00:35:38,435
                MOM?            


518
00:35:57,489 --> 00:35:59,422
        [ Sighs ]               


519
00:35:59,491 --> 00:36:01,825
        <i> [ Cell Phone Rings ]</i>   


520
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:08,665
                <i> [ Phone Beeps ]</i>
    STARR HERE.                 


521
00:36:08,733 --> 00:36:11,233
        IT'S SUSAN GRANGER.     
        YOUR ENVELOPE IS HERE.  


522
00:36:11,302 --> 00:36:13,336
    I'M ON MY WAY.              


523
00:36:13,404 --> 00:36:17,673
    [ Tires Screeching ]        
<i>[ Miss Parker ] YOU KNOW, SYD,</i>  
<i>I OUGHTA HAND IT TO HIM.</i>        


524
00:36:17,742 --> 00:36:21,144
HE ALMOST KEPT ME               
OUT OF THE PICTURE              
LONG ENOUGH.                    


525
00:36:21,213 --> 00:36:25,148
- HE WANTS TO KNOW THE TRUTH.   
- HE CAN'T, AND YOU KNOW IT.    


526
00:36:25,216 --> 00:36:28,084
            HMM.                


527
00:36:29,654 --> 00:36:32,188
    IT'S ONLY BECAUSE           
    OF HIS HEART.               


528
00:36:32,256 --> 00:36:36,058
    - WHAT?                     
    - THAT WE ARE THIS CLOSE,   
      MISS PARKER.              


529
00:36:36,127 --> 00:36:40,664
<i>JAROD KNEW THAT IF HE SENT</i>      
<i>THAT PHOTOGRAPH ONLINE,</i>         


530
00:36:40,732 --> 00:36:42,665
        WE'D FIND HIM.          


531
00:36:42,733 --> 00:36:45,735
<i>HE'S WILLING TO RISK EVERYTHING</i> 
<i>FOR AN IDENTITY,</i>                


532
00:36:45,803 --> 00:36:48,571
        FOR A LIFE.             


533
00:36:50,642 --> 00:36:52,909
    THAT'S WHAT I'M COUNTING ON.


534
00:36:54,579 --> 00:36:56,846
        [ Tires Screech ]       


535
00:37:00,151 --> 00:37:03,153
I THOUGHT YOU SHOULD BE         
THE ONE TO OPEN IT.             


536
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:09,292
            I'M SO NERVOUS.     
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>                  


537
00:37:09,361 --> 00:37:12,728
IT ISN'T EVERY DAY              
YOU FIND OUT WHO YOU ARE.       
<i>[ Clamoring ]</i>                   


538
00:37:12,797 --> 00:37:15,898
    WHAT IS GOING ON OUT HERE?  
    WHO ARE YOU PEOPLE?         


539
00:37:15,967 --> 00:37:18,634
        - WHERE IS HE?          
        -<i> [ Gun Cocks ]</i>         


540
00:37:18,703 --> 00:37:20,937
            I WON'T ASK AGAIN.  


541
00:37:21,006 --> 00:37:24,073
    <i> SAM. SAM, HE'S GOING</i>       
    <i> TO THE ROOF!</i>               


542
00:37:25,544 --> 00:37:29,612
            STOP, OR I SWEAR    
            I'LL SHOOT YOU      
            IN THE BACK!        


543
00:37:38,590 --> 00:37:40,790
<i>JAROD!</i>                          


544
00:37:43,662 --> 00:37:45,561
<i>SAM, GET HIM.</i>                   


545
00:37:47,532 --> 00:37:51,468
    YOU SENT THIS, DIDN'T YOU?  
I WAS WITH YOU,                 
MISS PARKER.                    


546
00:37:56,608 --> 00:37:58,908
                SO CLOSE...     


547
00:37:58,977 --> 00:38:01,277
            AND YET SO FAR.     


548
00:39:05,610 --> 00:39:08,611
        HI.                     
        THIS IS OFFICER STARR.  


549
00:39:08,679 --> 00:39:11,580
        I WAS WONDERING IF YOU  
        COULD DO ME A FAVOR.    


550
00:39:24,562 --> 00:39:27,897
[ Bishop ] WE GOT 15 MINUTES    
BEFORE THE SECURITY CAR         
COMES BACK AROUND.              


551
00:39:27,966 --> 00:39:30,966
    - YOU GOT THE ALARM CODE,   
      RIGHT, FRANK?             
    - YEAH.                     


552
00:39:31,035 --> 00:39:34,837
I'LL SHUT OFF THE JUICE,        
THEN CLIP THE VIDEO LINES       
TO THE SURVEILLANCE CAMERAS.    


553
00:39:34,906 --> 00:39:37,907
    ONCE WE'RE INSIDE, FRANKIE'S
    GONNA GO TO THE MANAGER'S   
    OFFICE AND GET THE GEMS.    


554
00:39:37,975 --> 00:39:40,242
        YOU HIT THE GOLD CASES. 
        I'LL KEEP AN EYE        
        ON THE FRONT.           


555
00:39:40,311 --> 00:39:42,679
    - WHAT IF THE SECURITY GUARD
      IS EARLY?                 
    - HE WON'T BE.              


556
00:39:42,747 --> 00:39:45,448
- WHAT IF YOU'RE WRONG?         
- IF I'M WRONG, THEY'RE DEAD.   


557
00:39:45,517 --> 00:39:48,518
        <i> THE CLOCK IS RUNNING,</i>  
        <i> GENTLEMEN.</i>             
        <i> LET'S DO THIS THING.</i>   


558
00:39:58,763 --> 00:40:00,897
    ALL RIGHT, GUYS.            
    LET'S DO THIS.              


559
00:40:00,965 --> 00:40:03,900
FRANK, YOU ALL RIGHT?           
    <i> I GOT THE MANAGER'S OFFICE.</i>


560
00:40:03,968 --> 00:40:07,904
        STARR.                  
        COINS, RINGS AND CHAINS,
        ALL RIGHT?              


561
00:40:07,972 --> 00:40:11,474
STAY AWAY FROM                  
THE STUPID COSTUME CRAP.        
LET'S DO IT.                    


562
00:40:13,444 --> 00:40:16,112
    - [ Imitates Gunshot ]      
    - WHAT ARE YOU DOING?       


563
00:40:16,181 --> 00:40:20,283
<i>I WAS JUST WONDERING</i>            
<i>HOW MARVIN KEMBROOK FELT</i>        
<i>THE NIGHT HE DIED.</i>              


564
00:40:20,352 --> 00:40:22,485
                [ Scoffs ]      


565
00:40:22,553 --> 00:40:25,321
        ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.   
        WE'LL TALK ABOUT THAT   
        LATER, OKAY?            


566
00:40:25,390 --> 00:40:27,323
<i>HE ANSWERS AN ALARM.</i>            


567
00:40:27,391 --> 00:40:31,027
HIS HEART IS POUNDING           
AT THE POTENTIAL DANGER.        


568
00:40:31,096 --> 00:40:35,398
    HE FEELS AFRAID,            
    WITH GOOD REASON.           


569
00:40:35,466 --> 00:40:39,702
<i>HE JUST GOT HIS LIFE BACK.</i>      
<i> HE JUST FIGURED OUT WHO HE WAS.</i>


570
00:40:39,770 --> 00:40:42,905
    HE JUST REDISCOVERED        
    HIS FAMILY.                 


571
00:40:42,974 --> 00:40:47,443
IMAGINE HIS RELIEF              
WHEN HE GETS THERE AND FINDS TWO
POLICE OFFICERS ON THE SCENE.   


572
00:40:47,512 --> 00:40:50,813
<i>THE GOOD GUYS.</i>                  


573
00:40:50,882 --> 00:40:53,849
    HIS RELIEF DIDN'T LAST      
    VERY LONG, DID IT?          


574
00:40:56,321 --> 00:40:59,789
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST             
FOR THE MURDER                  
OF MARVIN KEMBROOK.             


575
00:40:59,858 --> 00:41:04,093
            MAYBE I DON'T WANT  
            TO BE ARRESTED.     
[ Gun Clicks ]                  


576
00:41:07,165 --> 00:41:09,098
YOU'RE GOING TO JAIL.           


577
00:41:09,167 --> 00:41:11,400
<i>YOU AND MEYERS.</i>                 


578
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:15,171
            ALL RIGHT, STARR.   
            I'M JUST GONNA PUT  
            THE GUN DOWN.       


579
00:41:15,240 --> 00:41:17,540
            <i> HEY, WHAT THE HELL</i> 
            <i> IS GOING ON?</i>       


580
00:41:25,116 --> 00:41:27,450
        SORRY ABOUT THAT, JAROD.


581
00:41:27,519 --> 00:41:29,451
            <i> I DON'T DO JAIL.</i>   


582
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,787
                TOO MANY MOUTHS 
                TO FEED.        


583
00:41:31,856 --> 00:41:33,789
OH, MY GOD.                     


584
00:41:33,858 --> 00:41:36,325
            <i> CALL IT IN, FRANK.</i> 


585
00:41:36,394 --> 00:41:40,329
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED              
TO TELL 'EM?                    
            TELL 'EM THE TRUTH. 


586
00:41:40,398 --> 00:41:43,399
    TELL 'EM ONE OF OUR FINEST  
    WAS GUNNED DOWN TRYING      
    TO PREVENT A ROBBERY.       


587
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:52,975
<i>[ Bishop ] WE TURNED UP</i>         
<i>THE ALLEY HERE AND SAW SOMEBODY</i> 
<i>RUNNING OUT THE BACK DOOR.</i>      


588
00:41:53,044 --> 00:41:55,711
<i>FRANK AND I WENT INSIDE,</i>        
<i>IDENTIFIED OURSELVES</i>            
<i>AS OFFICERS,</i>                    


589
00:41:55,780 --> 00:41:58,214
        BUT THE PLACE WAS EMPTY 
        EXCEPT FOR THE BODY.    


590
00:41:58,283 --> 00:42:00,249
        THE BODY?               


591
00:42:00,318 --> 00:42:03,319
        OFFICER STARR APPARENTLY
        WAS THE FIRST ONE       
        ON THE SCENE.           


592
00:42:03,388 --> 00:42:06,655
        <i> WE CAME BACK OUTSIDE</i>   
        <i> AND SEARCHED</i>           
        <i> THE ADJACENT AREA,</i>     


593
00:42:06,724 --> 00:42:09,558
                BUT THE SHOOTER 
                WAS LONG GONE.  


594
00:42:09,627 --> 00:42:13,329
IS THAT THE WAY IT HAPPENED?    
MEYERS!                         


595
00:42:13,398 --> 00:42:15,498
IS THAT THE WAY IT HAPPENED?    


596
00:42:18,436 --> 00:42:20,369
    YEAH. YEAH,                 
    THAT'S HOW IT HAPPENED.     


597
00:42:22,673 --> 00:42:25,475
    SHOW ME.                    


598
00:42:25,543 --> 00:42:28,277
        YES, MA'AM.             


599
00:42:46,097 --> 00:42:49,365
<i>LET'S GET THE LAB BOYS DOWN HERE</i>
<i>TO CHECK OUT THAT SLUG.</i>         


600
00:42:49,434 --> 00:42:52,101
<i>[ Officer ]</i>                     
<i>RIGHT AWAY, DETECTIVE.</i>          


601
00:42:52,170 --> 00:42:55,304
    CARE TO REVISE YOUR STORY,  
    OFFICER BISHOP?             


602
00:42:55,373 --> 00:42:59,275
THE BODY WAS LYING RIGHT HERE.  
I SWEAR IT. I SAW IT MYSELF.    


603
00:42:59,344 --> 00:43:01,043
                    KEYS.       


604
00:43:02,446 --> 00:43:06,248
    - KEYS?                     
    - LET'S HAVE A LOOK IN      
      THE TRUNK OF YOUR CAR.    


605
00:43:12,023 --> 00:43:14,257
        [ Engine Running ]      


606
00:43:14,326 --> 00:43:17,994
        - LET'S ROLL!           
        - HOLD ON TIGHT!        


607
00:43:18,063 --> 00:43:19,995
        I'M LEGAL!              


608
00:43:20,064 --> 00:43:22,065
                <i> [ Laughing ]</i>   


609
00:43:34,612 --> 00:43:37,112
<i>YOU'RE UNDER ARREST</i>             
<i>FOR THE MURDER</i>                  
<i>OF MARVIN KEMBROOK.</i>             


610
00:43:37,181 --> 00:43:39,181
<i>YOU HAVE THE RIGHT</i>              
<i>TO REMAIN SILENT.</i>               


611
00:43:39,250 --> 00:43:41,250
<i>IF YOU GIVE UP THE RIGHT</i>        
<i>TO REMAIN SILENT,</i>               


612
00:43:41,319 --> 00:43:44,420
<i>ANYTHING YOU SAY CAN AND WILL</i>   
<i>BE USED AGAINST YOU</i>             
<i>IN A COURT OF LAW.</i>              


613
00:43:44,489 --> 00:43:47,356
<i>YOU HAVE THE RIGHT</i>              
<i>TO SPEAK WITH AN ATTORNEY--</i>     
    [ Imitates Gunshot ]        


614
00:44:10,147 --> 00:44:14,484
<i>JAROD WAS IN YOUR SIGHT.</i>        
<i>YOU COULD'VE KILLED HIM.</i>        
<i>WHAT MADE YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND?</i> 


615
00:44:16,820 --> 00:44:20,489
I JUST MISSED, SYDNEY.          
NO MORE, NO LESS.               


616
00:44:22,226 --> 00:44:25,193
                <i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>


617
00:44:25,262 --> 00:44:28,430
            HELLO. JAROD.       


618
00:44:28,499 --> 00:44:31,667
I TOLD YOU                      
WHEN I WAS 11 YEARS OLD         
THAT I WOULD NEVER GIVE UP,     


619
00:44:31,736 --> 00:44:33,669
AND I NEVER WILL.               


620
00:44:33,738 --> 00:44:37,339
I KNOW YOU WON'T, JAROD.        
MISS PARKER WON'T EITHER.       


621
00:44:37,408 --> 00:44:40,009
GOOD-BYE, SYDNEY.               
    HOLD IT.                    


622
00:44:40,078 --> 00:44:42,144
JUST TELL ME ONE THING,         
JAROD.                          


623
00:44:42,213 --> 00:44:44,080
WHAT DO THE NUMBERS MEAN?       
    WHAT?                       


624
00:44:44,148 --> 00:44:46,415
        10:19.                  


625
00:44:46,484 --> 00:44:49,218
        IT'S WHO I AM, SYDNEY.  


626
00:44:49,287 --> 00:44:51,553
        IT'S WHAT YOU MADE ME.  


627
00:44:51,623 --> 00:44:53,622
[ Line Clicks,                  
  Dial Tone Hums ]              


628
00:45:01,432 --> 00:45:03,433
[ Chuckles ]                    


629
00:45:12,810 --> 00:45:14,810
WHERE WILL HE GO NOW?           


630
00:45:18,382 --> 00:45:23,119
                    SOUTH.      
WHAT MAKES YOU SO SURE?         


631
00:45:23,187 --> 00:45:25,587
                    INSTINCT.   


632
00:45:25,656 --> 00:45:29,157
<i>♪♪ [ Brass Band: "O Canada" ]</i>   


633
00:45:30,461 --> 00:45:32,395
        [ Clucks Tongue ]       


634
00:46:11,870 --> 00:46:12,868
            [ Mews ]            


